The morphologies of the BNNS and aerogel samples were characterized using a SEM (Hitachi TM3030) and TEM (JEOL JEM 2010). The thickness and size of BNNS were measured on an atomic force microscope (AFM, NanoScope IIIa/Dimension 3100), as shown in Supplementary Fig. 24. The elemental compositions and chemical structure of BNNS were examined using the X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS, Axis Ultra DLD), as shown in Supplementary Fig. 25. The functional groups on BNNS, WPU aerogels, and BNNS/WPU composite aerogels were studied using the FTIR (Bruker Vertex 70 Hyperion 1000). The apparent density (ρ) of aerogels was calculated by weighing the samples and measuring their volumes. The porosity (P) of aerogels was determined by P=1−ρρ0×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
